. Problems with DOM

1.Slow Performance : Frequent direct DOM updates are slow and affect page speed.

2.Complex UI Handling : Managing dynamic content with manual DOM manipulation is difficult.

3.Hard to Maintain : Large DOM-based code becomes confusing and hard to manage.


. Advantages of React

1.Better Performance : React uses Virtual DOM to update only changed parts.

2.Reusable Components : Code can be reused, saving time and effort.

3.Easy UI Management : Declarative approach makes UI simple and predictable.